# API Guard Platform — Implementation Plan

## Overview

Build a production-grade API proxy platform where users register APIs, receive proxy endpoints, and get rate limiting, quota enforcement, and usage analytics — all powered by Spring Boot 4 microservices with RabbitMQ async event processing.

## Architecture Diagram

```mermaid
graph TB
    Client["Client App"] -->|API Key in Header| GW["Gateway Service :8080"]
    GW -->|Rate Limit Check| Redis["Redis :6379"]
    GW -->|Fetch API Config| AMS["API Management Service :8081"]
    GW -->|Proxy Request| Origin["Origin API"]
    GW -->|Publish Usage Event| RMQ["RabbitMQ :5672"]
    RMQ -->|Consume Events| US["Usage Service :8082"]
    US -->|Store Metrics| PG["PostgreSQL :5432"]
    US -->|Quota Exceeded| RMQ
    AMS -->|CRUD APIs, Keys, Plans| PG
    US -->|Webhook Notification| WH["Webhook Endpoint"]

    subgraph Infrastructure
        Redis
        RMQ
        PG
    end

    subgraph Microservices
        GW
        AMS
        US
    end
```

